.TH Holberton_Project 02 "25 November 2020" "VI.0" "Simple Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
.B
- Simple Shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B
Simple Shell is is a program that runs in the similar manner to a shell command-line interpreter.

.B Overview

The simple shell is a simplified iteration of a command line interpreter, similar to 
.B bash or 
.B dash. 
.I FORMAT [ARGUMENT]...
.SH OPTIONS
.B Simple Shell
operates in both 
.I interactive 
and 
.I non-interactive
 mode. When initiated,
.B simple shell
uses the commands that are specified in that particular progam
.SH ARGUMENTS
The first argument, argument 0 is understood to be the command to be run by 
.B simple shell
and arguments following as modifiers or options.
.SH INVOCATION
.B simple shell
may be invoked with the same functionality in 
.I interactive 
or 
.I non-interactive 
mode.  User may quit the program by typing "exit" on the command line.


.B Example
.IP

$./shell

simple@shell$pwd

/home/vagrant/simple_shell

simple@shell$

simple@shell$exit

$


.SH RESERVED WORDS
.B exit: 
exits the shell.

.B env: 
prints the environment variables


.SH FILES
.I mainsish.c 
- Contains the int main(void) function, entry point.

.I error_message.c
- Contains functions that creates messages appropriate to specific errors:
.B _puterror, build_error_message, end_of_file, fork_fail

.I strtok_example.c 
- Contains function that stores commands in double pointer: 
.B find_command_length, array_form_strtok functions.

.I helper_function.c 
- Contains all helper functions:
.B _strncpy,_strlen_const,_strcmp,_strlen,_strncpyconst

.I child_processes.c
- Contains additional processes required by multiple files
.B command_is_null,exit_out,env_out,parent_free_buff_commands,c_path

.SH BUGS
Report 
.B simple shell 
